1
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:35,840
Hug her! Hug her!

2
00:02:35,920 --> 00:02:37,920
How could you go on stage
instead of me, you brat!

3
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:39,640
Stop!

4
00:02:39,720 --> 00:02:40,600
PREVIOUS EPISODE

5
00:02:40,680 --> 00:02:42,680
You're just a driver!
How could you go on stage instead of me?

6
00:02:43,560 --> 00:02:44,720
Drugs?

7
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:46,880
There must be a drug dealer
at the company.

8
00:02:47,760 --> 00:02:49,680
-You're dead!
-Mr. Singha!

9
00:02:51,040 --> 00:02:53,480
-Village Head, run!
-Hurry! Move!

10
00:02:53,560 --> 00:02:55,880
I want you to forgive me, Puna.

11
00:02:55,960 --> 00:02:57,600
I forgive you.

12
00:02:58,360 --> 00:02:59,840
But I won't trust you again.

13
00:03:02,880 --> 00:03:09,240
<i>I want to be famous worldwide</i>
<i>Hoping luck will come, standing by</i>

14
00:03:09,320 --> 00:03:15,720
<i>Maybe if I get famous, I'll get lucky</i>
<i>And a police officer will fall for me</i>

15
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:18,560
<i>I want to be famous</i>

16
00:03:19,160 --> 00:03:21,720
<i>I want to be famous</i>

17
00:03:22,680 --> 00:03:25,840
<i>I want to be famous</i>

18
00:03:25,920 --> 00:03:28,360
<i>I want to be famous</i>

19
00:03:43,040 --> 00:03:45,960
Thank you!

20
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:51,600
Thank you all so much. Thank you.

21
00:03:53,440 --> 00:03:54,880
So many flowers! Thank you!

22
00:03:56,040 --> 00:04:00,960
-Maria, these are for you.
-Thank you so much for all your support!

23
00:04:01,040 --> 00:04:03,200
That performance just now was so cute,

24
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:05,520
especially the song you sang
with the male singer.

25
00:04:05,600 --> 00:04:06,720
Puna.

26
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:08,800
What's the name of the male singer
you sang with?

27
00:04:09,640 --> 00:04:11,920
His name's Chaiya.

28
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:14,560
Actually, he was just singing
to fill in the time.

29
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:16,560
Well,

30
00:04:16,640 --> 00:04:19,480
even if it was just a filler,
he's got a good voice, right?

31
00:04:19,560 --> 00:04:22,560
Yes! All the comments are saying
they want him to sing again.

32
00:04:22,640 --> 00:04:23,760
Did you know?

33
00:04:23,840 --> 00:04:27,040
You and Chaiya are trending
as a fan-favorite pair?

34
00:04:27,120 --> 00:04:28,200
Are you aware of that?

35
00:04:29,520 --> 00:04:30,680
A fan-favorite pair?

36
00:04:31,320 --> 00:04:32,720
Yes!

37
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:35,720
Right now, your social media buzz is huge.

38
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:55,320
Can we take a photo?

39
00:05:02,560 --> 00:05:04,840
Mr. Kitti, what's up? What's going on?

40
00:05:04,920 --> 00:05:09,080
Well, sir. I'm going
to have to cancel the delivery.

41
00:05:09,160 --> 00:05:11,000
What? Why?

42
00:05:12,240 --> 00:05:16,280
Something unexpected came up.
I need to sort out the problem here first.

43
00:05:16,360 --> 00:05:20,280
What the heck? I came all the way
and now you want to cancel?

44
00:05:20,360 --> 00:05:22,600
It's really necessary, sir.

45
00:05:22,680 --> 00:05:25,080
Necessary? What's necessary?

46
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:26,920
Are you trying to mess with me?

47
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:28,320
The deposit's already paid!

48
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:29,600
Calm down, sir.

49
00:05:30,160 --> 00:05:31,880
It's not like that.

50
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,040
Don't think I don't know about Boss Noo.

51
00:05:39,280 --> 00:05:40,720
If history repeats itself,

52
00:05:41,480 --> 00:05:42,520
you know what'll happen,

53
00:05:43,160 --> 00:05:44,600
don't you?

54
00:05:46,160 --> 00:05:47,840
No need to threaten me, sir.

55
00:05:48,480 --> 00:05:51,160
Whatever you've got, I've got it too.

56
00:05:51,840 --> 00:05:54,160
But now's not the time to fight.

57
00:05:54,240 --> 00:05:55,320
We could all get caught.

58
00:06:11,760 --> 00:06:13,480
-Chit.
-Yes?

59
00:06:14,440 --> 00:06:17,240
Tell Tod and Wong
to meet at the parking lot.

60
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:18,960
Yes, Boss.

61
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:29,720
STUDIO SEVEN

62
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:30,880
Sergeant Au's calling.

63
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:33,280
Pick it up.

64
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:34,360
What's up, Sergeant Au?

65
00:06:35,880 --> 00:06:37,960
Boss Jiang is about to leave.

66
00:06:38,680 --> 00:06:40,160
No drug delivery tonight.

67
00:06:40,760 --> 00:06:41,760
<i>I think they've realized the situation.</i>

68
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:45,880
They probably caught on.

69
00:06:47,320 --> 00:06:48,640
Okay, you tail them first.

70
00:06:49,240 --> 00:06:50,480
I'll handle things on this side.

71
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:52,400
Understood.

72
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:57,840
Any updates?

73
00:06:58,400 --> 00:06:59,880
It’s a wash tonight, Chaiya.

74
00:07:00,640 --> 00:07:01,920
They're not sending the drugs.

75
00:07:05,120 --> 00:07:06,080
Not really.

76
00:07:07,280 --> 00:07:09,560
If they haven't delivered yet, that means

77
00:07:09,640 --> 00:07:10,640
they're still in the car.

78
00:07:12,280 --> 00:07:13,440
Wait.

79
00:07:13,520 --> 00:07:14,600
Call Captain Tom.

80
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:16,120
He can make the move.

81
00:07:32,560 --> 00:07:34,480
How'd it go? Did you get them?

82
00:07:35,160 --> 00:07:36,160
They got away.

83
00:07:37,480 --> 00:07:39,520
You guys are hopeless

84
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:40,960
for letting them get away.

85
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:47,800
Oh, Captain.

86
00:07:49,880 --> 00:07:51,240
What brings you here?

87
00:07:52,360 --> 00:07:54,760
-We need to search the car.
-Search the car?

88
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:57,120
Do you have a warrant?

89
00:07:57,200 --> 00:07:58,920
Of course. Here it is.

90
00:08:05,960 --> 00:08:07,920
-Well.
-Hey.

91
00:08:09,160 --> 00:08:10,400
What's going on here?

92
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:12,600
The police want to search the car.

93
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:15,240
Want to search the car?

94
00:08:16,280 --> 00:08:18,160
Sure. There's nothing in it, just props.

95
00:08:23,400 --> 00:08:25,000
Hey, why are you opening it?

96
00:08:25,800 --> 00:08:28,360
We've got nothing to hide.
There's nothing in the car.

97
00:08:32,679 --> 00:08:33,919
Then I'll search the car.

98
00:08:35,480 --> 00:08:40,520
Go ahead. But I'll notify the owner first.

99
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:41,640
You stay here.

100
00:08:43,039 --> 00:08:44,280
You, go get Sonrak.

101
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:47,640
Got it. I'll bring him here.

102
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:55,480
Everyone else, stand by the car
with your hands up.

103
00:08:55,560 --> 00:08:56,800
Okay.

104
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:04,240
Search them.

105
00:09:20,400 --> 00:09:21,400
Puna…

106
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:24,560
STUDIO SEVEN

107
00:09:26,240 --> 00:09:27,960
You're leaving already?

108
00:09:28,040 --> 00:09:29,240
Yes.

109
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:30,840
How are you getting home?

110
00:09:31,440 --> 00:09:32,680
Don't worry.

111
00:09:33,320 --> 00:09:35,640
She'll be going home with me.

112
00:09:40,240 --> 00:09:41,560
Puna!

113
00:09:42,840 --> 00:09:44,360
Check your phone!

114
00:09:44,440 --> 00:09:47,880
Right now, fans can't stop asking

115
00:09:47,960 --> 00:09:49,720
to see you and Chaiya perform.

116
00:09:50,960 --> 00:09:52,360
I didn't expect this at all.

117
00:09:52,960 --> 00:09:55,840
Yes, the buzz is huge right now.

118
00:09:55,920 --> 00:09:57,680
Some people are just destined for fame.

119
00:09:57,760 --> 00:10:00,040
Everything they do gets noticed.

120
00:10:01,560 --> 00:10:04,360
How about I contact the boss

121
00:10:04,440 --> 00:10:06,720
to bring Chaiya in as a singer?

122
00:10:07,520 --> 00:10:10,480
I think that's a great idea.
It'll make him famous for sure!

123
00:10:10,560 --> 00:10:13,760
Especially the song "My Request"
he sang just now.

124
00:10:20,080 --> 00:10:21,200
Mr. Sonrak.

125
00:10:22,160 --> 00:10:24,120
The police want to search your car.

126
00:10:26,160 --> 00:10:27,320
Search for what?

127
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:42,200
Well, I'll get going.

128
00:10:51,200 --> 00:10:53,280
Your company's impressive,

129
00:10:53,360 --> 00:10:55,440
hiring people to hype up comments online.

130
00:10:59,920 --> 00:11:01,520
Don't think I didn't notice.

131
00:11:13,160 --> 00:11:14,720
We didn't hire them, right?

132
00:11:15,480 --> 00:11:18,200
Of course not.
Our company doesn't do that.

133
00:11:19,160 --> 00:11:21,840
She's done it before,
so she assumes others do too.

134
00:11:21,920 --> 00:11:23,120
Don't worry about it.

135
00:11:25,440 --> 00:11:26,600
-Let's go.
-Okay.

136
00:11:34,480 --> 00:11:36,400
Found anything, Captain?

137
00:11:36,920 --> 00:11:38,080
Don't talk so much.

138
00:11:41,520 --> 00:11:42,360
What's in that box?

139
00:11:43,880 --> 00:11:46,280
That's just a prop box,
containing performance equipment.

140
00:11:46,360 --> 00:11:47,720
Can I take a look?

141
00:11:48,320 --> 00:11:49,520
No.

142
00:11:49,600 --> 00:11:52,720
If anything inside gets damaged,

143
00:11:52,800 --> 00:11:54,560
who's responsible?

144
00:11:55,280 --> 00:11:57,640
Fine. If the officers can't search it,

145
00:11:57,720 --> 00:11:59,760
you can open it yourselves.

146
00:12:00,960 --> 00:12:06,200
Captain, it's just performance props.
Why do you need to check it?

147
00:12:06,280 --> 00:12:07,400
But that box

148
00:12:07,480 --> 00:12:09,160
could be hiding something illegal.

149
00:12:09,240 --> 00:12:13,240
Either way, I have to open it today.
Otherwise, none of you go anywhere.

150
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:15,440
What are you all doing?

151
00:12:21,520 --> 00:12:24,640
Using your authority
to intimidate the public,

152
00:12:25,520 --> 00:12:26,720
aren't you ashamed?

153
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:28,560
I received a report

154
00:12:28,640 --> 00:12:31,040
that this car is carrying drugs,

155
00:12:31,120 --> 00:12:32,200
so I need to search it.

156
00:12:33,320 --> 00:12:36,440
Nowadays, warrants
don't even go through me?

157
00:12:36,520 --> 00:12:39,400
This is a central police warrant,
not local.

158
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:41,840
You don't need to worry.

159
00:12:42,920 --> 00:12:44,440
But this is my jurisdiction.

160
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:47,240
At least show some respect.

161
00:12:52,680 --> 00:12:54,240
Are you going to search my car?

162
00:12:57,160 --> 00:12:59,560
The police say there are drugs
in your car.

163
00:12:59,640 --> 00:13:03,360
We confirmed nothing's there,
but they still want to search.

164
00:13:05,080 --> 00:13:06,680
This is blatant disrespect.

165
00:13:06,760 --> 00:13:10,240
We should livestream it,
so the fans can put pressure on them.

166
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:13,880
No need, Chang. Put it away.

167
00:13:14,720 --> 00:13:16,440
Go ahead, Officer. Search the car.

168
00:13:20,160 --> 00:13:21,680
Wait, Sonrak.

169
00:13:22,360 --> 00:13:23,440
Think carefully.

170
00:13:24,200 --> 00:13:27,080
If you don't want them to search,
I'll testify for you.

171
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:33,320
Stop causing trouble.
Otherwise, I'll have you investigated.

172
00:13:35,040 --> 00:13:36,720
It's fine, Uncle.

173
00:13:36,800 --> 00:13:39,880
There's nothing illegal in my car.
Officer, feel free to search.

174
00:13:39,960 --> 00:13:42,040
Check any corner, any compartment,

175
00:13:42,120 --> 00:13:43,000
you're welcome.

176
00:13:49,760 --> 00:13:51,040
Tod, Wong.

177
00:13:51,640 --> 00:13:53,680
Don't stop the police.

178
00:13:53,760 --> 00:13:55,240
The car owner has given permission.

179
00:13:57,720 --> 00:13:58,920
Come on, Captain.

180
00:13:59,600 --> 00:14:02,040
I'll help if you want to check any box.

181
00:14:02,120 --> 00:14:03,240
You stay out of this.

182
00:14:04,160 --> 00:14:05,960
Step aside. The police will do the search.

183
00:14:09,440 --> 00:14:10,520
Search it.

184
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:31,040
Nothing suspicious. No drugs
or illegal items in the car.

185
00:14:31,120 --> 00:14:32,520
Nothing anywhere else either.

186
00:14:33,760 --> 00:14:35,240
See, Officer?

187
00:14:35,320 --> 00:14:37,840
My car only carries performance equipment.

188
00:14:41,240 --> 00:14:43,200
Everyone knows

189
00:14:44,200 --> 00:14:45,680
I absolutely hate drugs.

190
00:14:48,960 --> 00:14:51,840
Next time, check
your information properly.

191
00:14:52,680 --> 00:14:55,240
Don't let people say you're sloppy.

192
00:14:56,360 --> 00:14:57,800
This could damage

193
00:14:58,360 --> 00:15:00,360
Mr. Sonrak's reputation.

194
00:15:00,920 --> 00:15:04,920
If Mr. Sonrak files a complaint,
I'll testify.

195
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:07,240
I don't support

196
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:10,200
police harassing civilians.

197
00:15:11,960 --> 00:15:13,280
It's fine, Sergeant.

198
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:17,280
But I hope this won't happen again.

199
00:15:19,720 --> 00:15:21,200
Anything else bothering you?

200
00:15:26,240 --> 00:15:27,040
No, sir.

201
00:15:27,680 --> 00:15:29,800
Then get out.

202
00:15:30,840 --> 00:15:31,800
All of you, move!

203
00:15:53,880 --> 00:15:54,960
Let's go.

204
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:02,200
Alright, let's go.

205
00:16:02,840 --> 00:16:05,000
I'll wait for Dad first.

206
00:16:05,760 --> 00:16:07,200
He's parked over there.

207
00:16:08,280 --> 00:16:09,800
What about Sophie and Joey?

208
00:16:10,800 --> 00:16:13,440
Not sure. Probably sulking
after getting scolded.

209
00:16:14,400 --> 00:16:16,720
If they keep this up,
they don't need to come to work.

210
00:16:18,640 --> 00:16:20,320
What do you mean?

211
00:16:21,400 --> 00:16:22,720
I mean they're fired.

212
00:16:24,120 --> 00:16:26,960
I don't tolerate people like this.
Don't let me see them again.

213
00:16:29,080 --> 00:16:31,600
Yes. I'll go now.

214
00:16:33,640 --> 00:16:35,840
-After you, Mr. Sonrak.
-Wait.

215
00:16:37,040 --> 00:16:38,320
I'll drive.

216
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:42,440
-You don't need to get involved.
-Sure, Chang. Go ahead, all yours.

217
00:16:43,960 --> 00:16:45,560
You two, go do your thing.

218
00:16:48,800 --> 00:16:49,880
Especially you.

219
00:16:53,280 --> 00:16:54,560
Please, get in.

220
00:17:02,680 --> 00:17:03,840
Let's go find Captain Tom.

221
00:17:05,280 --> 00:17:06,800
Alright, let's go.

222
00:17:13,119 --> 00:17:14,240
Captain, wait!

223
00:17:17,520 --> 00:17:18,599
What about the goods?

224
00:17:21,880 --> 00:17:23,280
They were in the car before.

225
00:17:23,359 --> 00:17:24,839
I don't know when they went missing.

226
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:27,119
I can confirm.

227
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:29,840
I saw the goods in that box.

228
00:17:30,600 --> 00:17:32,560
It was my fault I didn't watch the car.

229
00:17:32,640 --> 00:17:34,120
If they don't meet tonight,

230
00:17:34,760 --> 00:17:36,200
where will the goods end up?

231
00:17:37,960 --> 00:17:41,520
I'll investigate and find out
where they were moved.

232
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:50,000
<i>I'm loving this!</i>

233
00:17:50,760 --> 00:17:53,600
Did you see that captain's face?
He looked so defeated.

234
00:17:53,680 --> 00:17:56,880
Yeah, I saw. You're amazing, Chit.

235
00:17:56,960 --> 00:17:59,480
Without you, we'd be done for.

236
00:18:03,880 --> 00:18:05,560
So, you two,

237
00:18:05,640 --> 00:18:07,080
where did you hide the goods?

238
00:18:09,680 --> 00:18:12,240
Those two moved the stuff
to Village Head Prueng's car.

239
00:18:13,120 --> 00:18:15,120
Then just put it back where it was.

240
00:18:16,720 --> 00:18:17,720
But I've got a plan.

241
00:18:41,480 --> 00:18:43,360
-All set?
-All set, bro.

242
00:18:45,320 --> 00:18:48,320
So the goods
are still in Village Head Prueng's car.

243
00:18:53,120 --> 00:18:56,240
But now, I have no idea where he is.

244
00:18:56,320 --> 00:18:58,640
His daughter's still at the event.

245
00:18:58,720 --> 00:19:00,800
He'll show up for sure.

246
00:19:01,440 --> 00:19:02,840
Shall we check the car?

247
00:19:03,680 --> 00:19:04,800
-Let's go.
-Let's go.

248
00:19:22,680 --> 00:19:24,080
Where's Dad?

249
00:19:26,960 --> 00:19:29,000
Ugh, he left the car
with the windows down.

250
00:19:41,040 --> 00:19:44,000
-<i>Maria.</i>
-Dad! Where are you?

251
00:19:44,080 --> 00:19:45,360
<i>Don't say anything yet.</i>

252
00:19:45,440 --> 00:19:46,600
Just start the car.

253
00:19:46,680 --> 00:19:48,240
You have the spare key, right?

254
00:19:49,480 --> 00:19:52,720
Yes. What's going on?

255
00:19:52,800 --> 00:19:54,800
Drive out first, quickly.

256
00:19:54,880 --> 00:19:56,520
I'll meet you at the road entrance.

257
00:19:56,600 --> 00:19:57,760
<i>I'll explain there.</i>

258
00:19:58,360 --> 00:19:59,600
Okay!

259
00:20:21,520 --> 00:20:22,400
Hey.

260
00:20:22,480 --> 00:20:24,760
Hurry, follow them! Let's go.

261
00:20:28,160 --> 00:20:29,200
What do we do?

262
00:20:29,840 --> 00:20:30,960
Follow them.

263
00:20:56,960 --> 00:20:58,080
Go, quickly!

264
00:20:59,120 --> 00:21:01,040
What's going on, Dad? What happened?

265
00:21:01,120 --> 00:21:03,080
Those drug dealers,

266
00:21:03,160 --> 00:21:04,240
they're after me!

267
00:21:04,840 --> 00:21:05,920
What?

268
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:08,320
Don't ask yet. Just drive!

269
00:21:13,360 --> 00:21:16,280
Hey! These are drugs!

270
00:21:17,240 --> 00:21:19,320
How did they end up in our car, Dad?

271
00:21:19,840 --> 00:21:23,240
I don't know. It must be them.

272
00:21:23,320 --> 00:21:24,520
Go!

273
00:21:37,080 --> 00:21:38,080
Get out!

274
00:21:39,280 --> 00:21:40,520
I said get out!

275
00:21:56,560 --> 00:21:57,800
Don't mess with me!

276
00:21:58,400 --> 00:22:00,040
It's necessary, Miss Maria.

277
00:22:00,760 --> 00:22:03,680
You and Village Head
brought this on yourselves.

278
00:22:04,840 --> 00:22:07,560
You're drug dealers.
I'm reporting this to Mr. Singha!

279
00:22:08,120 --> 00:22:11,720
Go ahead. If you think
Mr. Singha doesn't know,

280
00:22:11,800 --> 00:22:13,320
feel free to report us.

281
00:22:19,080 --> 00:22:20,840
So these drugs belong to him?

282
00:22:21,440 --> 00:22:22,400
Want to know?

283
00:22:23,080 --> 00:22:24,720
I can take you to him.

284
00:22:26,360 --> 00:22:29,800
Don't do anything to us.
We won't say a word.

285
00:22:29,880 --> 00:22:32,680
That's exactly what people
who squeal always say.

286
00:22:37,040 --> 00:22:38,040
Go!

287
00:22:38,840 --> 00:22:41,480
-You two, follow them and catch them!
-Let's go!

288
00:22:41,560 --> 00:22:42,600
Maria.

289
00:22:44,840 --> 00:22:47,080
Put the mask on and help Maria.

290
00:22:47,680 --> 00:22:48,720
I'll handle things over here.

291
00:23:18,480 --> 00:23:20,800
-Wong, move the goods.
-Got it.

292
00:23:50,760 --> 00:23:52,080
Where did they disappear to so fast?

293
00:23:57,640 --> 00:23:59,560
Dad, are they really going to kill us?

294
00:24:00,840 --> 00:24:03,040
If we stay like this, we won't make it.

295
00:24:03,960 --> 00:24:05,280
Then what do we do?

296
00:24:05,960 --> 00:24:07,040
We have to split up.

297
00:24:07,120 --> 00:24:09,760
Head to the temple,
then meet at the pavilion.

298
00:24:09,840 --> 00:24:11,640
After that, we'll figure it out. Go!

299
00:24:12,600 --> 00:24:14,280
-Okay.
-Hurry!

300
00:24:35,120 --> 00:24:36,120
Where are you?

301
00:24:42,200 --> 00:24:43,240
Come out!

302
00:24:56,840 --> 00:24:57,800
Hey!

303
00:25:06,680 --> 00:25:07,920
Hey!

304
00:25:10,160 --> 00:25:11,280
Who are you?

305
00:25:21,560 --> 00:25:22,520
Where are you headed?

306
00:25:26,440 --> 00:25:28,000
-Ugh!
-Hey!

307
00:25:34,280 --> 00:25:35,120
Yeah.

308
00:25:35,720 --> 00:25:36,920
Something's definitely going on.

309
00:25:37,920 --> 00:25:39,120
Let's go.

310
00:26:18,440 --> 00:26:20,040
Hey! What are you doing?

311
00:26:20,120 --> 00:26:21,800
Do you want to get yourself killed?
Keep it down!

312
00:26:22,640 --> 00:26:23,640
How do you know?

313
00:26:25,320 --> 00:26:27,360
I followed you, so I saw everything.

314
00:26:29,840 --> 00:26:32,680
-Whoa! Chit, Tod!
-Hey! Chit!

315
00:26:32,760 --> 00:26:35,480
-You okay? Get up.
-No.

316
00:26:39,360 --> 00:26:40,600
They went that way.

317
00:26:42,000 --> 00:26:43,160
Here, gun. Follow them.

318
00:26:44,080 --> 00:26:47,240
Let me help you. Let's go.

319
00:26:48,880 --> 00:26:49,800
Someone's coming!

320
00:26:49,880 --> 00:26:51,280
-Let's hide!
-Okay.

321
00:26:56,560 --> 00:26:58,000
-Hey!
-Stop!

322
00:27:00,680 --> 00:27:03,120
-It's me.
-Chaiya!

323
00:27:03,800 --> 00:27:04,880
It's me, Manat.

324
00:27:06,720 --> 00:27:07,720
They're following us!

325
00:27:08,400 --> 00:27:09,360
-Hurry!
-Let's go!

326
00:27:09,440 --> 00:27:10,520
-Let's go!
-Go!

327
00:27:20,360 --> 00:27:21,760
Damn it!

328
00:27:21,840 --> 00:27:24,640
Chit, you handle this spot.

329
00:27:24,720 --> 00:27:26,200
The rest, follow me!

330
00:27:32,720 --> 00:27:34,240
Get in, fast!

331
00:27:46,520 --> 00:27:47,640
Hey!

332
00:27:49,760 --> 00:27:52,400
Geez! Wong, get the car, quick!

333
00:27:52,480 --> 00:27:53,480
Yes!

334
00:28:08,280 --> 00:28:10,880
-Maria, make sure you stay safe.
-Hey!

335
00:28:14,760 --> 00:28:16,000
Where do you think you're going?

336
00:28:22,360 --> 00:28:23,760
Oh, come on!

337
00:28:24,440 --> 00:28:25,800
Hey! Don't tell me…

338
00:28:25,880 --> 00:28:27,960
Yeah. We're out of gas.

339
00:28:28,600 --> 00:28:29,520
What now, Chaiya?

340
00:28:32,000 --> 00:28:32,960
Over there.

341
00:28:34,120 --> 00:28:35,480
What are you planning to do?

342
00:28:35,560 --> 00:28:38,600
Switch cars. Go to that one, quick!

343
00:29:12,720 --> 00:29:14,320
Hey, watch out.

344
00:29:19,160 --> 00:29:20,520
I don't see anyone.

345
00:29:23,160 --> 00:29:24,720
They've got to be around here.

346
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:38,520
Hey, Chart!

347
00:29:39,680 --> 00:29:40,520
-Hey.
-It's me.

348
00:29:41,600 --> 00:29:43,120
It's you, Jiew?

349
00:29:43,840 --> 00:29:44,960
What's up, Chart?

350
00:29:47,240 --> 00:29:49,880
I'm tracking someone right now.

351
00:29:49,960 --> 00:29:51,280
Who is it, Chart?

352
00:29:51,360 --> 00:29:53,880
A singer named Maria. Do you know her?

353
00:29:55,200 --> 00:29:56,360
A singer named Maria?

354
00:29:58,480 --> 00:30:00,400
I know her. Her song is a hit.

355
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:02,400
She's beautiful too.

356
00:30:03,160 --> 00:30:04,920
Why do you ask, Chart?

357
00:30:05,000 --> 00:30:06,360
She and her crew

358
00:30:07,200 --> 00:30:09,120
have seen our drug operation.

359
00:30:09,200 --> 00:30:11,400
Huh? Maria?

360
00:30:11,920 --> 00:30:12,760
Yes.

361
00:30:12,840 --> 00:30:14,880
If you find them,

362
00:30:15,480 --> 00:30:16,320
you can take them out.

363
00:30:17,240 --> 00:30:18,640
Mr. Kitti gave permission.

364
00:30:19,800 --> 00:30:20,840
Got it.

365
00:30:21,440 --> 00:30:23,680
I just need to make a delivery first.

366
00:30:24,280 --> 00:30:26,560
It's tough now, so many checkpoints.

367
00:30:27,360 --> 00:30:29,600
Alright. Stay alert.

368
00:30:30,760 --> 00:30:31,720
Let's go.

369
00:30:48,080 --> 00:30:50,000
The owner of this truck knows them.

370
00:31:04,520 --> 00:31:07,560
We have to wait until this car stops
before we find a way to get down.

371
00:31:08,920 --> 00:31:10,680
But Maria's being chased.

372
00:31:11,840 --> 00:31:13,280
We have to get out in a busy area.

373
00:31:14,080 --> 00:31:15,680
Then find another ride to the city.

374
00:31:25,560 --> 00:31:26,800
What is this?

375
00:31:38,280 --> 00:31:39,560
The stuff.

376
00:31:40,480 --> 00:31:41,320
What is it?

377
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:42,960
Drugs.

378
00:31:44,160 --> 00:31:45,240
Drugs?

379
00:31:46,600 --> 00:31:49,640
Why do I keep running into drugs tonight?

380
00:31:49,720 --> 00:31:51,080
Manat.

381
00:31:51,160 --> 00:31:54,160
Call central police immediately.
Intercept this car.

382
00:31:55,120 --> 00:31:56,160
On it.

383
00:32:17,320 --> 00:32:19,200
Where's your daughter?

384
00:32:21,320 --> 00:32:22,520
Tell me!

385
00:32:27,000 --> 00:32:28,560
Don't hurt Maria.

386
00:32:30,600 --> 00:32:32,520
Who helped your daughter?

387
00:32:34,160 --> 00:32:36,280
Someone helped Maria?

388
00:32:38,080 --> 00:32:40,080
Don't play dumb!

389
00:32:40,160 --> 00:32:41,160
Who?!

390
00:32:41,240 --> 00:32:42,680
I don't know.

391
00:32:46,160 --> 00:32:47,160
Chit.

392
00:32:49,440 --> 00:32:50,520
You don't know?

393
00:33:02,640 --> 00:33:06,160
What about Maria, Joey, and Sophie?

394
00:33:07,400 --> 00:33:11,280
They got away,
but we've got people chasing them now.

395
00:33:12,360 --> 00:33:13,680
If you find them, take care of it.

396
00:33:14,480 --> 00:33:15,640
Don't wait for my orders.

397
00:33:16,160 --> 00:33:17,160
Got it.

398
00:33:18,040 --> 00:33:19,560
What about Village Head Prueng?

399
00:33:20,160 --> 00:33:21,600
What do you want me to do with him?

400
00:33:21,680 --> 00:33:22,920
Don't kill him yet.

401
00:33:24,200 --> 00:33:26,160
Keep him as bait to lure Maria out.

402
00:33:26,680 --> 00:33:28,360
Okay, understood.

403
00:33:40,920 --> 00:33:43,760
GPS is on. They're coming.

404
00:33:46,520 --> 00:33:48,560
They? Who are they?

405
00:33:53,080 --> 00:33:54,000
Who exactly are you?

406
00:33:57,200 --> 00:33:59,320
We're good people,
definitely not bad guys.

407
00:34:03,600 --> 00:34:04,840
Don't tell me

408
00:34:05,560 --> 00:34:06,480
you guys are cops.

409
00:34:12,159 --> 00:34:13,360
Well, you got it.

410
00:34:16,920 --> 00:34:17,840
Unbelievable.

411
00:34:20,320 --> 00:34:21,880
Hey, you guys.

412
00:34:22,800 --> 00:34:24,840
We need to put on these clothes first.

413
00:34:24,920 --> 00:34:28,000
We have to disguise ourselves.
Chart and his men are still after us.

414
00:34:33,639 --> 00:34:35,920
We should put on these clothes
to change our look.

415
00:34:36,560 --> 00:34:38,199
So we don't get spotted.

416
00:34:39,159 --> 00:34:40,480
Change?

417
00:34:42,239 --> 00:34:43,639
Change here?

418
00:34:44,199 --> 00:34:46,400
I think just wearing them
over our clothes is enough.

419
00:35:23,280 --> 00:35:24,680
I actually like this outfit.

420
00:35:27,960 --> 00:35:28,960
Really?

421
00:35:42,680 --> 00:35:44,280
Found a little extra surprise, Chaiya.

422
00:35:59,280 --> 00:36:00,640
Wow, that's plenty!

423
00:36:06,720 --> 00:36:08,040
No.

424
00:36:25,040 --> 00:36:26,080
Dad.

425
00:36:29,280 --> 00:36:30,120
You look serious.

426
00:36:30,720 --> 00:36:32,080
What's bothering you?

427
00:36:35,120 --> 00:36:36,720
It's about tonight's concert.

428
00:36:40,360 --> 00:36:43,360
You're worried that Chaiya
is performing instead, aren't you?

429
00:36:44,440 --> 00:36:45,440
Yes, Dad.

430
00:36:47,280 --> 00:36:48,840
Tonight the buzz is huge.

431
00:36:49,920 --> 00:36:51,200
People are talking about him more than me.

432
00:36:52,320 --> 00:36:56,040
What can he do? He's just a filler singer.

433
00:36:56,120 --> 00:36:58,320
What if someone hires him
as a professional singer?

434
00:37:00,280 --> 00:37:01,600
He'll become my rival.

435
00:37:02,800 --> 00:37:04,120
I can't accept that.

436
00:37:05,240 --> 00:37:06,400
He can't do that.

437
00:37:07,520 --> 00:37:08,720
I'll handle it.

438
00:37:09,320 --> 00:37:10,760
What will you do, Dad?

439
00:37:11,760 --> 00:37:12,840
Well.

440
00:37:14,280 --> 00:37:15,920
Tonight, for the song he's singing,

441
00:37:16,760 --> 00:37:18,320
if I find out who wrote it,

442
00:37:19,440 --> 00:37:20,640
I'll buy it for you to perform yourself.

443
00:37:22,920 --> 00:37:24,080
As for Chaiya,

444
00:37:24,840 --> 00:37:26,360
I'll sign him to the company,

445
00:37:27,000 --> 00:37:29,840
but just shelve him.
He won't be your rival anymore.

446
00:37:30,440 --> 00:37:31,640
And Puna?

447
00:37:32,960 --> 00:37:33,920
What?

448
00:37:35,080 --> 00:37:36,680
Dad.

449
00:37:42,520 --> 00:37:43,800
I love Puna.

450
00:37:47,560 --> 00:37:49,040
I want her to be mine.

451
00:37:52,360 --> 00:37:54,400
Can you help me? Please, Dad.

452
00:37:54,480 --> 00:37:55,480
Please help me.

453
00:37:55,560 --> 00:37:57,320
Well, after the show,

454
00:37:57,400 --> 00:38:00,760
I tried to talk to her backstage,
but I couldn't face her. Please, Dad.

455
00:38:01,920 --> 00:38:02,960
Please help me.

456
00:38:05,760 --> 00:38:07,320
If you want my help, sure.

457
00:38:08,280 --> 00:38:09,840
I'll see what I can do.

458
00:38:12,720 --> 00:38:15,880
Are you serious, Dad?
You're not lying to me, right?

459
00:38:16,760 --> 00:38:17,760
Sonrak.

460
00:38:18,720 --> 00:38:20,040
Ever since you were a kid,

461
00:38:20,600 --> 00:38:21,560
whatever you wanted,

462
00:38:22,440 --> 00:38:24,040
I've always found a way to get it for you.

463
00:38:27,240 --> 00:38:29,520
-Where should we go today?
-Let's grab something to eat.

464
00:38:29,600 --> 00:38:30,800
Hey!

465
00:38:30,880 --> 00:38:32,920
You're Chai,
the singing contest champ, right?

466
00:38:33,000 --> 00:38:34,720
Yes, what is it?

467
00:38:41,240 --> 00:38:42,480
You're not allowed to beat Mr. Sonrak

468
00:38:42,560 --> 00:38:44,400
in this year's singing contest!

469
00:38:44,480 --> 00:38:45,840
Got it?

470
00:38:45,920 --> 00:38:47,760
No, I don't understand.

471
00:38:47,840 --> 00:38:49,840
Why are you doing this to me?

472
00:38:51,160 --> 00:38:53,880
Do you want to get killed? Huh?

473
00:38:55,840 --> 00:38:58,320
Yes, I'll let Mr. Sonrak win

474
00:38:58,400 --> 00:39:00,160
in the singing contest.

475
00:39:00,240 --> 00:39:02,000
Please don't hurt me!

476
00:39:09,760 --> 00:39:12,680
DARATHONG MUSIC

477
00:39:14,680 --> 00:39:15,600
Okay.

478
00:39:17,160 --> 00:39:19,040
Dad!

479
00:39:19,760 --> 00:39:22,280
Dad! I won the contest!

480
00:39:22,360 --> 00:39:24,360
Dad! I won the contest!

481
00:39:24,440 --> 00:39:26,640
Hey, congratulations!

482
00:39:26,720 --> 00:39:28,160
You did it!

483
00:39:29,280 --> 00:39:32,600
But if you hadn't helped me,
Chai would've competed,

484
00:39:32,680 --> 00:39:35,400
and I wouldn't have won.
What did you do, Dad?

485
00:39:36,400 --> 00:39:38,600
Well, you don't need to know.

486
00:39:39,200 --> 00:39:41,120
I just went and talked to him nicely.

487
00:39:41,200 --> 00:39:43,160
Thank you, Dad! I love you!

488
00:39:43,800 --> 00:39:45,560
I love you so much, Dad!

489
00:39:45,640 --> 00:39:47,600
I love you so much too, Sonrak.

490
00:39:47,680 --> 00:39:48,560
Remember,

491
00:39:49,080 --> 00:39:52,120
I'd never let you lose.

492
00:39:54,240 --> 00:39:55,520
Thank you, Dad.

493
00:39:57,080 --> 00:39:59,320
Thanks, Dad. Really, thank you!

494
00:40:03,160 --> 00:40:05,920
Dad, whose car is this? It's brand new.

495
00:40:09,120 --> 00:40:12,040
Whoever asked, it must be theirs.

496
00:40:14,280 --> 00:40:17,880
Dad, don't tell me

497
00:40:17,960 --> 00:40:19,200
this is my car!

498
00:40:22,120 --> 00:40:25,080
Hey! Who else could it be?

499
00:40:25,800 --> 00:40:28,160
A brand-new car like this

500
00:40:28,240 --> 00:40:32,640
can only go to the winner
of this year's singing contest.

501
00:40:35,880 --> 00:40:37,560
Thank you, Dad! Thank you so much!

502
00:40:41,240 --> 00:40:44,960
You know, right?
I've never done anything to let you down.

503
00:40:48,000 --> 00:40:49,080
Yes, Dad.

504
00:40:50,320 --> 00:40:51,480
Thank you.

505
00:41:47,160 --> 00:41:48,280
Hey, Jiew!

506
00:41:49,600 --> 00:41:50,800
Yes, Boss Jiang.

507
00:42:18,040 --> 00:42:19,760
Chaiya, you've got double standards, huh?

508
00:42:24,240 --> 00:42:25,480
Right on time!

509
00:42:29,760 --> 00:42:31,520
Good. I like this.

510
00:42:31,600 --> 00:42:33,280
Thank you, Boss Jiang.

511
00:42:33,960 --> 00:42:36,480
We have to keep time
because drug deliveries

512
00:42:37,280 --> 00:42:38,720
are our business.

513
00:42:41,440 --> 00:42:42,760
They're drug traffickers.

514
00:42:44,000 --> 00:42:45,760
Looks like Singha's network.

515
00:42:46,440 --> 00:42:49,640
I'm really sorry, everyone,
for putting us in this mess.

516
00:42:50,800 --> 00:42:52,240
Don't think like that.

517
00:42:52,320 --> 00:42:55,440
Now we all know
about their drug operation,

518
00:42:55,520 --> 00:42:57,160
and we'll deal with it together.

519
00:43:02,440 --> 00:43:04,360
Hey! Who are you guys?

520
00:43:09,640 --> 00:43:10,760
We're just filming content.

521
00:43:11,600 --> 00:43:12,560
-Yes.
-That's right

522
00:43:12,640 --> 00:43:14,000
I don't believe you.

523
00:43:14,080 --> 00:43:15,560
Anyone trespassing here dies!

524
00:43:24,400 --> 00:43:26,080
Jiew! Anyone trespassing, kill them all!

525
00:43:26,160 --> 00:43:27,040
Follow them!

526
00:43:28,080 --> 00:43:29,120
Go!

527
00:43:47,080 --> 00:43:49,120
-Come on, move!
-Hurry!

528
00:43:54,040 --> 00:43:56,200
Hey! Follow them!

529
00:43:57,360 --> 00:43:59,520
Hey! Get the drug transport car out!

530
00:44:00,280 --> 00:44:01,640
Yes, sir.

531
00:44:01,720 --> 00:44:04,440
Trying to run? Anyone who knows my secret

532
00:44:04,520 --> 00:44:05,680
must die!

533
00:44:07,240 --> 00:44:08,240
-Quick!
-Let's go!

534
00:44:19,200 --> 00:44:20,120
This is bad.

535
00:44:21,880 --> 00:44:24,800
Hey! That's Maria! Kill her!

536
00:44:32,520 --> 00:44:34,280
-Go!
-Go!

537
00:44:37,640 --> 00:44:38,800
Follow them!

538
00:44:42,000 --> 00:44:42,960
Hey!

539
00:44:44,480 --> 00:44:46,160
Hey! Hit them hard!

540
00:44:55,720 --> 00:44:57,640
Hey, throw another one!

541
00:45:05,520 --> 00:45:07,160
This way! Quick, this way!

542
00:45:07,760 --> 00:45:09,360
Hey! Follow me!

543
00:45:25,480 --> 00:45:27,840
They won't stop chasing us.

544
00:45:29,760 --> 00:45:32,360
What do we do? They're after me.

545
00:45:34,440 --> 00:45:36,040
-Should I--
-Maria!

546
00:45:36,120 --> 00:45:37,640
Don't think like that.

547
00:45:37,720 --> 00:45:39,920
No way we're letting you go.

548
00:45:40,640 --> 00:45:43,320
Calm down. There has to be another way.

549
00:46:03,960 --> 00:46:05,120
I'll lure them another way.

550
00:46:06,360 --> 00:46:07,360
We'll meet up after.

551
00:46:07,440 --> 00:46:08,640
Got it.

552
00:46:09,920 --> 00:46:11,320
Be careful.

553
00:46:26,960 --> 00:46:29,160
Hey! Where did they go?

554
00:46:33,400 --> 00:46:34,360
They've disappeared.

555
00:46:35,120 --> 00:46:37,160
How is that possible?

556
00:46:40,240 --> 00:46:41,880
Jiew! They're over there! Go!

557
00:46:41,960 --> 00:46:42,960
Hey, follow me!

558
00:46:48,720 --> 00:46:50,040
Chaiya!

559
00:46:51,520 --> 00:46:52,480
Those gunshots?

560
00:46:53,200 --> 00:46:54,080
I fired to distract them.

561
00:46:55,280 --> 00:46:56,360
So what do we do now?

562
00:46:56,440 --> 00:46:59,320
I don't know,
but we have to get out of here.

563
00:46:59,400 --> 00:47:00,720
-Move!
-Go!

564
00:47:08,880 --> 00:47:10,320
Where the hell did they go?

565
00:47:13,200 --> 00:47:14,400
They're gone, Boss.

566
00:47:14,480 --> 00:47:16,960
Damn it. We've been tricked.

567
00:47:24,760 --> 00:47:27,720
Hey! Who's that helicopter for?

568
00:47:40,920 --> 00:47:42,840
Quick! Get on the helicopter!

569
00:47:42,920 --> 00:47:44,360
-Go!
-Wait!

570
00:47:44,440 --> 00:47:45,640
Us?

571
00:47:46,280 --> 00:47:48,080
Me too?

572
00:47:48,680 --> 00:47:50,960
Yes, you. Get on quickly!

573
00:47:51,040 --> 00:47:52,640
-Go!
-Hey!

574
00:48:43,320 --> 00:48:44,480
They've got a helicopter.

575
00:48:45,160 --> 00:48:46,480
Who are they?

576
00:48:53,760 --> 00:48:56,040
They've got me.

577
00:48:56,640 --> 00:48:59,200
Don't worry. We'll go save your dad.

578
00:48:59,280 --> 00:49:00,520
They're watching like that,

579
00:49:01,280 --> 00:49:03,720
someone's definitely inside.

580
00:49:03,800 --> 00:49:05,920
NEXT EPISODE

581
00:49:08,640 --> 00:49:10,240
If you sell me the song,

582
00:49:11,120 --> 00:49:12,680
I'll promote it to the fullest.

583
00:52:21,800 --> 00:52:23,960
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
